{
	"nodes":[
		{"id":"title","type":"text","text":"# Radiology Node — Complete Pipeline\nEvery function call from image upload to rendered results.\n\n**Language boundary:** Rust (Tauri) orchestrates, Python (Stage 1 + Stage 2 + Model inference) executes.\n**Current state:** Python pipeline fully implemented. Frontend complete. Rust node is a stub. Tauri commands NOT YET IMPLEMENTED — this is the integration gap.","x":-200,"y":-2495,"width":560,"height":180,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"frontend_entry","type":"text","text":"### Frontend Entry\n`RadiologyContent.tsx`\n```\n// Step 1: User selects model\nsetSelectedModel(\"chest-xray\" | \"fracture\")\nsetStatus(\"selecting\")\n\n// Step 2: User drops image → Stage 1\nextractFile(file: File)\n  const arrayBuffer = await file.arrayBuffer()\n  const bytes = Array.from(new Uint8Array(arrayBuffer))\n  invoke<string>(\"extract_image\", {\n    fileName: file.name,\n    fileBytes: bytes,\n  })\n  → setStatus(\"confirming\")\n\n// Step 3: User confirms → Stage 2 + inference\nconfirmAndProcess()\n  invoke<string>(\"process_image\", {\n    fileName, fileBytes, model: selectedModel,\n  })\n```\nAlso: `handleDrop()` → `handleFiles()` → `extractFile()`","x":-200,"y":-2215,"width":560,"height":520,"color":"5"},
		{"id":"pipeline_runner","type":"text","text":"### Pipeline Runner\n`pipeline/mod.rs::run_pipeline<N: Node>`\n```rust\npub fn run_pipeline<N: Node>(\n    node: &N, input: N::ImportInput,\n) -> Result<OutputContract, PipelineError> {\n    let raw      = node.import(input)?;     // Layer 1\n    let unified  = node.unify(&raw)?;       // Layer 2\n    let evaluation = node.evaluate(&unified)?; // Layer 3\n    node.output(&raw, &unified, &evaluation)   // Layer 4\n}\n```\nSequential — each layer feeds the next.\nAny layer can fail with `PipelineError`.\n\n**Note:** For radiology, the Rust node is currently a stub.\nThe real work is done by `extract_image` / `process_image`\ncommands calling Python directly (bypassing the Node trait\npipeline until Rust layers are implemented).","x":-200,"y":-430,"width":560,"height":520,"color":"6"},
		{"id":"tauri_commands","type":"text","text":"### Tauri Commands (NOT YET IMPLEMENTED)\n`commands.rs` — needs 4 new commands:\n\n```rust\n// Stage 1: validate + store + metadata\n#[tauri::command]\npub async fn extract_image(\n    file_name: String,\n    file_bytes: Vec<u8>,\n) -> Result<String, String>\n// → spawn python3 run_imaging.py --stage1-only --json-stdout\n// → return Stage 1 JSON to frontend\n\n// Stage 2 + model inference\n#[tauri::command]\npub async fn process_image(\n    file_name: String,\n    file_bytes: Vec<u8>,\n    model: String,\n) -> Result<String, String>\n// → spawn python3 run_imaging.py --model {model} --json-stdout\n// → store result via FsNodeStorage\n// → return full JSON to frontend\n\n// History\n#[tauri::command]\npub async fn list_imaging_results() -> Result<String, String>\n\n#[tauri::command]\npub async fn load_imaging_result(\n    file_hash: String,\n) -> Result<String, String>\n```\n\nMust also register in `lib.rs` handler array.","x":-200,"y":-1560,"width":560,"height":840,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"integration_gap","type":"text","text":"### Integration Gap\n\n**What exists (fully working):**\n✓ Python imaging pipeline (`run_imaging.py` + all stages)\n✓ Two model adapters (TorchXRayVision + SigLIP2 fracture)\n✓ React UI (`RadiologyContent.tsx` with drag-drop,\n   model selection, confirmation, results display)\n✓ Rust stub node (compiles, returns placeholder data)\n✓ Node registered in `registry.ts`\n\n**What's missing (the bridge):**\n✗ Tauri command handlers in `commands.rs`:\n   - `extract_image` — Stage 1\n   - `process_image` — Stage 2 + inference\n   - `list_imaging_results` — history\n   - `load_imaging_result` — load by hash\n✗ Command registration in `lib.rs`\n✗ Subprocess calls to `python3 run_imaging.py`\n✗ Result storage via `FsNodeStorage`\n\n**To connect:** Follow the same pattern as\n`run_bloodwork` in `commands.rs` — save temp file,\nspawn Python subprocess, parse JSON stdout,\nstore via `FsNodeStorage`, return to frontend.","x":640,"y":-1460,"width":560,"height":640,"color":"3"},
		{"id":"model_selector","type":"text","text":"### Model Adapter Selection\n`run_imaging.py`\n\n```python\nif model == \"chest-xray\":\n    from imaging.models.torchxrayvision_model import predict\nelif model == \"fracture\":\n    from imaging.models.fracture_model import predict\n\nfindings = predict(standardised.pixels)\n```\n\n**Architecture:** Each model is a separate adapter module\nthat consumes the same `StandardisedImage.pixels`\n(H×W float64 [0,1]) and returns the same shape:\n```python\n[{\"pathology\": str, \"probability\": float, \"level\": str}, ...]\n```\n\nNew models are added as new modules without touching\nStage 1 or Stage 2. The pipeline is model-agnostic\nup to the inference step.","x":95,"y":2850,"width":480,"height":580,"color":"6"},
		{"id":"frontend_output","type":"text","text":"### Frontend: Render Results\n`RadiologyContent.tsx`\n\n```typescript\n// Parse JSON string from Tauri\nconst parsed: AnalysisResult = JSON.parse(jsonString);\nsetResult(parsed);\nsetStatus(\"done\");\nloadHistory();\n```\n\n**Result types:**\n```typescript\ninterface Finding {\n  pathology: string;\n  probability: number;  // 0.0–1.0\n  level: \"HIGH\" | \"MODERATE\" | \"LOW\" | \"MINIMAL\";\n}\n\ninterface AnalysisResult {\n  success: boolean;\n  record: { file_hash, stored_path, original_name, is_duplicate };\n  image_metadata: { width, height, channels, bit_depth, format, file_size_kb, is_grayscale };\n  model: string;\n  findings: Finding[];\n  summary: { high_probability[], moderate_probability[], total_pathologies_screened, flagged_count };\n}\n```\n\n**Rendered components:**\n1. **summaryBar** — filename, screened count, flagged count\n2. **Image preview** (if local blob URL exists)\n3. **resultsTable** — per finding:\n   ```\n   | Pathology | Probability | Score Bar | Level |\n   ```\n   - Probability bar with colour-coded fill\n   - HIGH → red, MODERATE → orange, LOW → green, MINIMAL → grey\n   - Rows highlighted for HIGH/MODERATE findings\n\n**History navigation:**\n- `loadHistory()` → `invoke(\"list_imaging_results\")` → parse records\n- `loadResult(hash)` → `invoke(\"load_imaging_result\", {fileHash})` → set result\n- On mount: auto-loads latest result if history exists","x":3265,"y":2720,"width":680,"height":960,"color":"5"},
		{"id":"unify_rust","type":"text","text":"## Layer 2: Unify (STUB)\n`nodes/radiology/mod.rs::unify()`\n```rust\nfn unify(raw: &RawData) -> Result<RadiologyData>\n```\n\nExtracts modality from raw JSON:\n```rust\nlet modality = raw.content\n    .get(\"modality\")\n    .and_then(|m| m.as_str())\n    .unwrap_or(\"unknown\")\n    .to_string();\n```\n\n→ `RadiologyData { modality, collection_date }`\n\n**Minimal stub.** Real unification happens in Python\n(`standardise_image`). The Rust unify layer would need\nto parse Stage 2's standardisation metadata if the\nNode trait pipeline is fully connected.","x":-730,"y":980,"width":530,"height":520,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"unify_types","type":"text","text":"### Unify Data Types\n`nodes/radiology/mod.rs`\n\n```rust\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]\npub struct RadiologyData {\n    pub modality: String,\n    pub collection_date: Option<String>,\n}\n```\n\n**Python StandardisedImage metadata:**\n```python\n{\n    \"original_height\": 2048,\n    \"original_width\": 2048,\n    \"standardised_height\": 2048,\n    \"standardised_width\": 2048,\n    \"was_converted_to_grayscale\": false,\n    \"was_orientation_corrected\": false,\n    \"dtype\": \"float64\",\n    \"intensity_range\": [0.0, 1.0]\n}\n```\n\n**Design principle:** Model-agnostic standardisation.\nStage 2 produces a clean [0,1] grayscale array.\nEach model adapter handles its own transforms\n(resize, scaling, channel duplication).","x":-730,"y":1770,"width":530,"height":680,"color":"5"},
		{"id":"stage2_standardise","type":"text","text":"## Python Stage 2: Unifying\n`imaging/unifying/normaliser.py::standardise_image()`\n```python\ndef standardise_image(file_path) -> StandardisedImage\n```\n\n**Step 1: EXIF orientation correction**\n```python\nwas_orientation_corrected = _has_exif_rotation(img)\nimg = ImageOps.exif_transpose(img)\n```\n\n**Step 2: Grayscale conversion**\n```python\nwas_converted = img.mode not in (\"L\", \"I\", \"F\")\nif was_converted:\n    img = img.convert(\"L\")\n```\n\n**Step 3: Normalise to [0, 1] float64**\n```python\narr = np.array(img, dtype=np.float64)\nif arr.max() > 1.0:\n    arr = arr / arr.max()  # handles 8-bit, 16-bit, etc.\n```\n\n**Step 4: Preserve original resolution**\nModels handle their own resize internally.\n\n→ `StandardisedImage`\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass StandardisedImage:\n    pixels: np.ndarray       # (H, W), float64, [0, 1]\n    original_height: int\n    original_width: int\n    standardised_height: int\n    standardised_width: int\n    was_converted_to_grayscale: bool\n    was_orientation_corrected: bool\n```","x":-730,"y":2660,"width":530,"height":960,"color":"6"},
		{"id":"model_torchxrv","type":"text","text":"### Model: TorchXRayVision\n`imaging/models/torchxrayvision_model.py`\n```python\ndef predict(standardised_pixels: np.ndarray) -> list[dict]\n```\n\n**Model:** `densenet121-res224-chex`\n**Task:** 18 chest pathology screening\n\n**Model-specific transforms:**\n1. Scale `[0,1] → [-1024, 1024]`\n   `img = (img - 0.5) * 2048`\n2. Add channel dim: `(H,W) → (1,H,W)`\n3. Resize + CenterCrop to 224×224\n4. Add batch dim: `(1,1,224,224)`\n\n**Inference:**\n```python\nmodel = xrv.models.DenseNet(weights=\"densenet121-res224-chex\")\nmodel.eval()\nwith torch.no_grad():\n    preds = model(tensor)\n```\n\n**18 pathologies screened:**\nAtelectasis, Consolidation, Infiltration, Pneumothorax,\nEdema, Emphysema, Fibrosis, Effusion, Pneumonia,\nPleural_Thickening, Cardiomegaly, Nodule, Mass,\nHernia, Lung Lesion, Fracture, Lung Opacity, Enlarged Cardiomediastinum\n\n**Severity classification:**\n```python\n≥ 0.7 → HIGH\n≥ 0.4 → MODERATE\n≥ 0.2 → LOW\n< 0.2 → MINIMAL\n```","x":-545,"y":4000,"width":760,"height":930,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"model_fracture","type":"text","text":"### Model: Fracture Detection\n`imaging/models/fracture_model.py`\n```python\ndef predict(standardised_pixels: np.ndarray) -> list[dict]\n```\n\n**Model:** `prithivMLmods/Bone-Fracture-Detection`\n**Architecture:** SigLIP2 (from HuggingFace)\n**Task:** Binary classification — Fractured vs Not Fractured\n**Accuracy:** ~83% on validation set\n\n**Model-specific transforms:**\n1. `[0,1] float64 → uint8 [0,255]`\n2. Grayscale → RGB PIL Image\n3. `AutoImageProcessor` handles resize\n\n**Inference:**\n```python\nprocessor = AutoImageProcessor.from_pretrained(MODEL_ID)\nmodel = AutoModelForImageClassification.from_pretrained(MODEL_ID)\ninputs = processor(images=pil_img, return_tensors=\"pt\")\nlogits = model(**inputs).logits\nprobs = softmax(logits, dim=1)\n```\n\n**Severity classification:**\nFor \"Fractured\":\n```python\n≥ 0.8 → HIGH\n≥ 0.5 → MODERATE\n≥ 0.3 → LOW\n< 0.3 → MINIMAL\n```\nFor \"Not Fractured\": always `MINIMAL`","x":455,"y":4000,"width":680,"height":890,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"stage1_output","type":"text","text":"### Stage 1 JSON Output\nReturned to Rust via stdout:\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"stage\": \"importing\",\n  \"record\": {\n    \"file_hash\": \"a1b2c3...\",\n    \"stored_path\": \"~/Documents/hOS/uploads/imaging/a1b2c3.png\",\n    \"original_name\": \"chest_xray.png\",\n    \"is_duplicate\": false\n  },\n  \"image_metadata\": {\n    \"width\": 2048,\n    \"height\": 2048,\n    \"channels\": 1,\n    \"bit_depth\": 8,\n    \"format\": \"PNG\",\n    \"file_size_kb\": 1024.5,\n    \"is_grayscale\": true,\n    \"has_exif\": false,\n    \"orientation\": null,\n    \"warnings\": []\n  },\n  \"quality\": {\n    \"warnings\": [],\n    \"warning_count\": 0\n  }\n}\n```\n\nFrontend parses this as `ExtractionResult` and\nshows confirmation screen with metadata chips.","x":-3249,"y":4760,"width":580,"height":820,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"full_output","type":"text","text":"### Full Pipeline JSON Output\nReturned to Rust via stdout (no `--stage1-only`):\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"stage\": \"complete\",\n  \"record\": {\n    \"file_hash\": \"a1b2c3...\",\n    \"stored_path\": \"~/Documents/hOS/uploads/imaging/a1b2c3.png\",\n    \"original_name\": \"chest_xray.png\",\n    \"is_duplicate\": false\n  },\n  \"image_metadata\": {\n    \"width\": 2048, \"height\": 2048,\n    \"channels\": 1, \"bit_depth\": 8,\n    \"format\": \"PNG\", \"file_size_kb\": 1024.5,\n    \"is_grayscale\": true\n  },\n  \"standardisation\": {\n    \"original_height\": 2048, \"original_width\": 2048,\n    \"standardised_height\": 2048, \"standardised_width\": 2048,\n    \"was_converted_to_grayscale\": false,\n    \"was_orientation_corrected\": false,\n    \"dtype\": \"float64\",\n    \"intensity_range\": [0.0, 1.0]\n  },\n  \"model\": \"densenet121-res224-chex\",\n  \"model_key\": \"chest-xray\",\n  \"findings\": [\n    { \"pathology\": \"Effusion\", \"probability\": 0.4523, \"level\": \"MODERATE\" },\n    { \"pathology\": \"Atelectasis\", \"probability\": 0.2341, \"level\": \"LOW\" }\n  ],\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"total_pathologies_screened\": 18,\n    \"flagged_count\": 2,\n    \"high_probability\": [],\n    \"moderate_probability\": [\"Effusion\"]\n  }\n}\n```","x":-3289,"y":5890,"width":660,"height":920,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"python_types","type":"text","text":"### Python Data Types\n```python\n# Stage 1: Importing\nImageMetadata {\n    width, height, channels, bit_depth,\n    format, file_size_kb, is_grayscale,\n    has_exif, orientation, warnings[]\n}\n     ↓ store_image()\nStorageResult {\n    file_hash, stored_path,\n    original_name, is_duplicate\n}\n\n# Stage 2: Unifying\nStandardisedImage {\n    pixels: np.ndarray  # (H,W) float64 [0,1]\n    original_height, original_width,\n    standardised_height, standardised_width,\n    was_converted_to_grayscale,\n    was_orientation_corrected\n}\n\n# Model output\nFinding {\n    pathology: str,\n    probability: float,  # 0.0–1.0\n    level: str           # HIGH/MODERATE/LOW/MINIMAL\n}\n```\n\nStage 1 validates + stores.\nStage 2 standardises (model-agnostic).\nModel adapters consume Stage 2 output.","x":-3239,"y":7170,"width":560,"height":680,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"confirmation_flow","type":"text","text":"### User Confirmation (Frontend)\n`RadiologyContent.tsx` — status: `confirming`\n\nAfter Stage 1, user sees:\n1. **Image preview** (local blob URL)\n2. **Metadata chips:** format, dimensions, channels, bit depth, file size\n3. **Quality warnings** (yellow banner if any)\n4. **Selected model** reminder\n5. **Actions:** Cancel | Confirm & Analyze\n\n```typescript\ninterface ExtractionResult {\n  success: boolean;\n  stage: string;\n  record: { file_hash, stored_path, original_name, is_duplicate };\n  image_metadata: {\n    width, height, channels, bit_depth, format,\n    file_size_kb, is_grayscale, has_exif, orientation,\n    warnings: string[]\n  };\n  quality: { warnings: string[], warning_count: number };\n}\n```\n\n**On confirm:** calls `confirmAndProcess()` → Stage 2 + inference.","x":-2185,"y":4880,"width":560,"height":580,"color":"5"},
		{"id":"step3_quality","type":"text","text":"### Step 3: Quality Assessment\n`run_imaging.py` (inline)\n\nAfter validate + store, compile quality report:\n```python\nresult = {\n    \"quality\": {\n        \"warnings\": metadata.warnings,\n        \"warning_count\": len(metadata.warnings),\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Quality warnings surfaced:**\n- Very small image (<100px) — may affect analysis\n- Non-grayscale — will be converted in Stage 2\n- EXIF rotation present — will be corrected\n- Duplicate file detected\n\nThis is where Stage 1 returns for user confirmation\nif `--stage1-only` is set.","x":-2629,"y":3830,"width":460,"height":520,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"evaluate_rust","type":"text","text":"## Layer 3: Evaluate (STUB)\n`nodes/radiology/mod.rs::evaluate()`\n```rust\nfn evaluate(_data: &RadiologyData) -> Result<EvaluationOutput>\n```\n\nCurrently returns empty evaluation:\n```rust\nEvaluationOutput {\n    critical_flags: vec![],\n    categories: HashMap::new(),\n    domain_scores: vec![],\n    condition_matches: vec![],\n    certainty: CertaintyGrade {\n        grade: CertaintyLevel::Insufficient,\n        confidence: 0.0,\n        missing_data: vec![\"Radiology node not yet implemented\"],\n        incompleteness_impact: \"Stub — no analysis performed\",\n    },\n    engine_versions: {\n        \"radiology_evaluator\": \"0.1.0-stub\"\n    },\n}\n```\n\n**Future:** Should consume model findings and:\n- Surface HIGH findings as `critical_flags`\n- Categorise findings by pathology type\n- Compute certainty from model confidence\n- Track `engine_versions` per model","x":1025,"y":990,"width":580,"height":780,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"pipeline_output","type":"text","text":"## Layer 4: Pipeline (Output) — STUB\n`nodes/radiology/mod.rs::output()`\n```rust\nfn output(\n    raw: &RawData,\n    data: &RadiologyData,\n    evaluation: &EvaluationOutput,\n) -> Result<OutputContract>\n```\n\n**Current stub:**\n```rust\nOutputContract {\n    node_id: \"radiology\",\n    schema_version: \"0.1.0\",\n    produced_at: String::new(),  // TODO: timestamp\n    collection_date: raw.collection_date,\n    unified_data: serde_json::to_value(data)?,\n    evaluation: evaluation.clone(),\n    metadata: ContractMetadata {\n        source_hash: raw.file_hash,\n        original_name: raw.original_name,\n        engine_versions: evaluation.engine_versions,\n        processing_notes: vec![\"Stub implementation\"],\n    },\n}\n```\n\n**Future:** Should include model findings in\n`unified_data` and proper timestamps.","x":3325,"y":960,"width":580,"height":780,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"storage","type":"text","text":"### Storage\n`commands.rs` + `pipeline/storage.rs`\n\nAfter `process_image()` returns from Python:\n```rust\n// 1. Get base directory\nlet base_dir = util::data_dir()?;\n   // → ~/Documents/hOS/\n\n// 2. Create node storage\nFsNodeStorage::new(&base_dir, \"radiology\")\n   // → create_dir_all(~/Documents/hOS/results/radiology/)\n\n// 3. Store analysis result\n// Store the Python JSON output as the result\n// keyed by file_hash from the Python response\n```\n\nFinal path: `~/Documents/hOS/results/radiology/{SHA-256}.json`\n\nCompartmentalised: each node owns its directory.\nOrchestrator reads contracts only, never node storage.\n\n**Note:** Currently not connected — Tauri commands\nnot yet implemented.","x":3345,"y":1920,"width":540,"height":580,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"storage_trait","type":"text","text":"### NodeStorage Trait\n`pipeline/storage.rs`\n```rust\ntrait NodeStorage {\n    fn store_contract(&self, contract) -> Result<()>;\n    fn load_contract(&self, hash) -> Result<OutputContract>;\n    fn list_contracts(&self) -> Result<Vec<String>>;\n}\n```\n\n**list_contracts():**\n```rust\nfs::read_dir(node_dir)\n    .filter(ext == \"json\")\n    .map(file_stem → hash string)\n```\n\n**load_contract(hash):**\n```rust\nlet path = node_dir / \"{hash}.json\"\nfs::read_to_string(path)\nserde_json::from_str::<OutputContract>(content)\n```\n\nShared trait — identical across all nodes.","x":2425,"y":1920,"width":600,"height":510,"color":"5"},
		{"id":"file_system","type":"text","text":"### File System Layout\n```\n~/Documents/hOS/\n├── uploads/\n│   └── imaging/\n│       └── {SHA-256}.{ext}    ← raw image (permanent)\n├── results/\n│   └── radiology/\n│       └── {SHA-256}.json     ← analysis result\n└── tmp/\n    └── (cleaned up after import)\n```\n\nNote: unlike bloodwork (which stores PDFs in\n`uploads/` root), imaging stores in\n`uploads/imaging/` subdirectory.\nFile extension is preserved (`.png`, `.jpg`, etc.).","x":4165,"y":1920,"width":500,"height":380,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"import_rust","type":"text","text":"## Layer 1: Import (STUB)\n`nodes/radiology/mod.rs::import()`\n\n**Currently a stub — returns placeholder data.**\n```rust\nfn import(input: RadiologyInput) -> Result<RawData>\n```\n→ Returns:\n```rust\nRawData {\n    source: \"radiology-stub\",\n    original_name: Some(input.file_name),\n    file_hash: None,\n    collection_date: None,\n    content: json!({\"modality\": input.modality, \"status\": \"stub\"}),\n}\n```\n\n**Future:** Should delegate to Python subprocess\n(like bloodwork does) via `util::find_script(\"run_imaging.py\")`\nwith `--stage1-only --json-stdout`.","x":-3249,"y":980,"width":480,"height":620,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"input_types","type":"text","text":"### Input Types\n`nodes/radiology/mod.rs`\n\n```rust\npub struct RadiologyInput {\n    pub file_name: String,\n    pub file_bytes: Vec<u8>,\n    pub modality: String,\n}\n```\n\n**Frontend model selection:**\n```typescript\ntype ModelKey = \"chest-xray\" | \"fracture\";\n\nconst MODELS = [\n  { key: \"chest-xray\",\n    label: \"Chest X-ray\",\n    description: \"18 pathology screening (TorchXRayVision)\" },\n  { key: \"fracture\",\n    label: \"Fracture Detection\",\n    description: \"Bone fracture classification (SigLIP2)\" },\n];\n```\n\n**Accepted file types:**\nPNG, JPEG, WebP, TIFF","x":-3249,"y":1730,"width":480,"height":580,"color":"5"},
		{"id":"python_entry","type":"text","text":"## Python Pipeline\n`data/run_imaging.py::run_pipeline()`\n\nThree-phase modular pipeline:\n```python\ndef run_pipeline(\n    image_path: str,\n    output_dir: str | None = None,\n    quiet: bool = False,\n    stage1_only: bool = False,\n    model: str = \"chest-xray\",\n) -> dict\n```\n\n**Usage from CLI:**\n```bash\npython3 run_imaging.py <image_path> \\\n    --json-stdout \\\n    --stage1-only \\     # for Stage 1 only\n    --model chest-xray   # or fracture\n    --output-dir ~/Documents/hOS/\n```\n\n**Available models:**\n```python\nAVAILABLE_MODELS = {\n    \"chest-xray\": {\n        \"name\": \"densenet121-res224-chex\",\n        \"description\": \"TorchXRayVision DenseNet — 18 chest pathologies\",\n    },\n    \"fracture\": {\n        \"name\": \"Bone-Fracture-Detection\",\n        \"description\": \"SigLIP2 fracture detection\",\n    },\n}\n```","x":-3249,"y":2630,"width":520,"height":770,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"step1_validate","type":"text","text":"### Step 1: validate_image()\n`imaging/importing/validator.py`\n```python\ndef validate_image(file_path) -> ImageMetadata\n```\n1. `Path(file_path).exists()` — file exists?\n2. `Image.open(path).verify()` — check corruption\n3. Format check: `fmt ∈ {PNG, JPEG, TIFF, WEBP, BMP}`\n4. Extract metadata:\n   - `width, height = img.size`\n   - `channels = _get_channels(img.mode)`\n   - `bit_depth = _get_bit_depth(img.mode)`\n   - `is_grayscale = mode ∈ {L, LA, I, F, 1, I;16}`\n   - `has_exif = bool(img.getexif())`\n   - `orientation = _get_exif_orientation(img)`\n5. Quality warnings:\n   - `width < 100 or height < 100` → small image\n   - `not is_grayscale` → will be converted\n   - `orientation != 1` → will be corrected\n\n→ `ImageMetadata { width, height, channels, bit_depth,`\n`format, file_size_kb, is_grayscale, has_exif,`\n`orientation, warnings[] }`\n\nRaises `ValueError` if unsupported/corrupt.","x":-3845,"y":3710,"width":480,"height":760,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"step2_store","type":"text","text":"### Step 2: store_image()\n`imaging/importing/storage.py`\n```python\ndef store_image(file_path, uploads_dir) -> StorageResult\n```\n1. `uploads.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)`\n2. `compute_hash(path):`\n   ```\n   sha256 = hashlib.sha256()\n   for chunk in iter(read 8192 bytes):\n       sha256.update(chunk)\n   return sha256.hexdigest()\n   ```\n3. `ext = path.suffix.lower()` (preserve format)\n4. `dest = uploads / f\"{file_hash}{ext}\"`\n5. `is_duplicate = dest.exists()`\n6. `shutil.copy2(path, dest)` if not duplicate\n\n→ `StorageResult { file_hash, stored_path, original_name, is_duplicate }`\n\nStorage: `~/Documents/hOS/uploads/imaging/{SHA-256}.{ext}`\n\nAlso supports `store_image_from_bytes(data, original_name)`\nfor receiving raw bytes from Tauri frontend.","x":-3249,"y":3750,"width":480,"height":680,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"evaluate_types","type":"text","text":"### Evaluate Types\n`pipeline/types.rs`\n\n```rust\nEvaluationOutput {\n    critical_flags: Vec<String>,\n    categories: HashMap<String, Vec<String>>,\n    domain_scores: Vec<DomainScore>,      // EMPTY\n    condition_matches: Vec<ConditionMatch>,// EMPTY\n    certainty: CertaintyGrade,\n    engine_versions: HashMap<String, String>,\n}\n\nDomainScore {        // NOT YET USED\n    system: String,  // e.g. \"torchxrayvision\"\n    score: f64,\n    interpretation: String,\n    components: Vec<String>,\n    version: String,\n}\n\nConditionMatch {     // NOT YET USED\n    condition: String,\n    criteria: Vec<CriterionResult>,\n    certainty: CertaintyGrade,\n}\n\nCertaintyGrade {\n    grade: High | Moderate | Low | Insufficient,\n    confidence: f64,  // 0.0–1.0\n    missing_data: Vec<String>,\n    incompleteness_impact: String,\n}\n```\n\nShared types — identical across all nodes.","x":1315,"y":-660,"width":600,"height":870,"color":"5"},
		{"id":"output_types","type":"text","text":"### Output Contract Types\n`pipeline/types.rs`\n\n```rust\nOutputContract {\n    node_id: String,\n    schema_version: String,\n    produced_at: String,\n    collection_date: Option<String>,\n    unified_data: serde_json::Value,\n    evaluation: EvaluationOutput,\n    metadata: ContractMetadata,\n}\n\nContractMetadata {\n    source_hash: Option<String>,\n    original_name: Option<String>,\n    engine_versions: HashMap<String, String>,\n    processing_notes: Vec<String>,\n}\n```\n\nThis is the **Orchestrator's only data source**.\nNodes never read each other's storage.","x":3305,"y":-417,"width":580,"height":590,"color":"5"},
		{"id":"node_trait","type":"text","text":"### Node Trait\n`pipeline/mod.rs`\n```rust\npub trait Node {\n    type ImportInput;\n    type UnifiedData;\n    fn node_id(&self) -> &str;\n    fn import(&self, input) -> Result<RawData>;\n    fn unify(&self, raw) -> Result<Self::UnifiedData>;\n    fn evaluate(&self, data) -> Result<EvaluationOutput>;\n    fn output(&self, raw, data, eval) -> Result<OutputContract>;\n}\n```\n`RadiologyNode` sets:\n- `ImportInput = RadiologyInput`\n- `UnifiedData = RadiologyData`\n- `node_id() = \"radiology\"`","x":-1440,"y":-387,"width":480,"height":530,"color":"5"},
		{"id":"util_fns","type":"text","text":"### Utilities\n`util.rs`\n\n**data_dir()**\n```rust\ndirs::home_dir() → join(\"Documents/hOS\")\nfs::create_dir_all(&dir)\n```\n\n**find_venv_python(script)**\n```\n1. script/../.venv/bin/python3\n2. /opt/anaconda3/bin/python3\n3. /opt/homebrew/anaconda3/bin/python3\n4. ~/anaconda3/bin/python3\n5. ~/miniconda3/bin/python3\n6. Fallback: \"python3\"\n```\n\n**find_script(name)**\n```\n1. exe/../../../data/{name}\n2. ../../data/{name}\n3. ../data/{name}\n4. data/{name}\n5. ~/Data/hOS/data/{name}\n```\n\nShared utilities — used by all nodes.","x":-3349,"y":-605,"width":680,"height":695,"color":"5"},
		{"id":"error_types","type":"text","text":"### Error Handling\n`pipeline/error.rs`\n```rust\nenum PipelineError {\n    Import(String),\n    Unify(String),\n    Evaluate(String),\n    Pipeline(String),\n    ExternalProcess(String),\n    Storage(String),\n}\n```\n\nAll layers return `Result<T, PipelineError>`.\nNo `.unwrap()` in production paths.\n\nPython errors surface via `ExternalProcess`:\n- `ValueError` from validator (unsupported format)\n- Subprocess non-zero exit code\n- JSON parse failure on stdout\n\nErrors propagate: Pipeline → commands → Tauri IPC → frontend `setErrorMsg()`","x":-4005,"y":1165,"width":400,"height":370,"color":"1"}
	],
